description.plain:
Pia Mia (born September 19, 1996) is an American singer, songwriter and model. In 2013, Pia was introduced to Chris Brown’s manager Abou “Bu” Thiam.

On December 3, 2013, Pia released her debut single “Red Love” from her first EP The Gift, which was later released for free on December 23, 2013.

In May of 2015, Pia started to work on her debut album, which she has not released yet. In early 2015, Pia released the album’s promotional single “Fuck With You” featuring G-Eazy. “Fuck With You" was originally the first single off her debut album, but it was later scrapped after underwhelming commercial performance.

On May 4, 2015, Pia released the new lead single for the debut album called “Do It Again” featuring Chris Brown and Tyga .

On December 15, 2017, Pia released her second EP The Gift 2 which is the follow up to 2013’s The Gift.
